      repository is licensed under the
      <a href="https://github.com/ReynoldsWJ55/thailand-liveability-index/blob/main/LICENSE">MIT License</a>.
      You can use, modify, and redistribute the code freely, including
      commercially, with attribution.
    </p>

    <h2>Public dataset — CC BY-NC 4.0</h2>
    <p>
      The methodology document, indicator definitions, scoring algorithm,
      data outputs (province-level scores, indicator meta), and other
      non-code content are licensed under
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/">Creative
      Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0)</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Free use cases under CC BY-NC 4.0:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Academic research, theses, and peer-reviewed publication</li>
      <li>Journalism and editorial coverage</li>
      <li>Personal, civic, and educational use</li>
      <li>Thai government and public-sector use</li>
      <li>Non-profit organizations whose use is non-commercial</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Commercial use — separate license required</h2>
    <p>
      Use of TLI's methodology, data outputs, indicator definitions, or
      any derived material in a product, service, or workflow primarily
      intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation requires
      a separate commercial license.
    </p>
    <p>
      Commercial-licensing inquiries:
      <a href="mailto:info@thailandliveabilityindex.com">info@thailandliveabilityindex.com</a>.
      See also
      <a href="https://github.com/ReynoldsWJ55/thailand-liveability-index/blob/main/LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md">LICENSE-COMMERCIAL.md</a>
      in the repository.
    </p>
    <p class="meta">
      Pricing and terms are negotiated per use case. Public commercial
      pricing is not yet published.
    </p>

    <h2>Trademark</h2>
    <p>
      The names "Thailand Liveability Index" and "TLI", together with
      any associated visual marks, are trademarks of the project
      maintainer. The MIT and CC BY-NC 4.0 licenses do not grant rights
